body:
I think for optional return values it is preferable to pass by pointer. Otherwise the caller code will read clumsy like

```cpp
Optional<int> foo;
GetInt(foo);
std::cout << * foo << std::endl;
```

As opposed to a simple

```cpp
int foo;
GetInt(&foo);
std::cout << foo << std::endl;

